<h2 id="hello-">Hello!</h2>
<p>I&#39;m Liam, a third-year Computer Science and Economics student at the University of Toronto.</p>
<p>In the past, I have worked on projects utilizing computer vision and colour/shape detection, hardware emulation, and networking technology, as well as recursive pathfinding algorithms and full-stack applications. You can find write ups on the most interesting ones here.</p>
<p>I have experience creating application dashboards and administrative consoles in Plotly Dash, implementing SQL databases into existing software, and automating the real world with computer vision.</p>
<p>Outside of coding, I enjoy running along Lake Ontario, photographing the world around me, and expressing myself through electronic music. Of which, you can also find on this site</p>
